### Establishing Target Variable 


To support predictive modeling, a target variable was created to represent high-value funnel progression. Leads that advanced to SQL, SQO, or WON are classified as successful outcomes.

Defining this target enables exploratory analysis to focus on how individual features differ between successful and unsuccessful leads, helping uncover meaningful correlations and patterns that inform feature selection and model design.

The unit of analysis for this project is an individual QAL lead. The target variable is binary, indicating whether a lead progressed to a high-value funnel stage (SQL, SQO, or WON).


```{r Target Variable}
#creating a target variable to use for future modeling. Target shows positive movement through the sales funnel.  

